->A variable is a name given to memory location for easily access of data
->Variables can keep changing value depending upon the instructions given by the programmer
->for declaring variable in java we use 'var' keyword
->By using var keyword it will be capable of storing any type of data.
//code snippet
public class Hellojva {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        var name="anu";
        var age=34;
        System.out.println("Name is"+ name);
        System.out.println("age is "+age);
    }

OPERATORS
->Operators are special symbols that perform specific operations on one,two or three operands and return their result.
TYPES:
1.Arithmetic operator
2.Relational operator
3.Logical operator
4.Bitwise operator
4.Ternary operator
    
